Self indulgent. If the story were portrayed in chronological order it
would be deemed trite. Neither of the principal characters is
particularly appetizing; they lack depth and developed characters other
than superficial traits.<br /><br />The secondary characters other than serving the need of explaining the
memory erasure do not drive the narrative and serve mainly as filler.<br /><br />Kaufman uses film as a form of freudian analysis instead of seeing a
psychiatrist. He might write better screenplays after having been
analyzed.<br /><br />On the other hand he might quit screen writing altogether if he
completed analysis.
